// BRU 4.97-in radial-inflow turbine map -- TOTAL-TO-TOTAL coordinates.
// NPSS turbine map ('Subelement TurbinePRmap S_map'): independents NpMap and PRmap
// (total-to-total Pt_in/Pt_out); tables TB_Wp, TB_eff output WpMap = Wp/0.486 and
// effMap = total eta_t(1->3). (PR is an input, not output.)
// PR_tt recovered from the total-to-static map via exit kinetic energy from the digitized
// eta_tt (Fig 11b) and eta_ts (Fig 11a) nu-curves -- no assumed exit Mach.
// Pairs directly with an NPSS/GasCycle total-to-total turbine expansion-ratio element.

Subelement TurbinePRmap S_map {
   PRmapDes = 1.645;
   NpMapDes = 1.000;
   // ReDes  = 76200.0;   // RNI = Re/ReDes; anchor = ARGON COLD-RIG design Re (TN D-5090). At the
   //   He-Xe ~10 kWe point RNI ~2 (hot mu at 1600F ~2.5x cuts Re, but the ~1.3 lb/s loop flow more
   //   than offsets) -> s_effRe ~1.01, a small FAVORABLE bump. See docs/turbine.md.

   Table TB_Wp(real NpMap, real PRmap) {
      NpMap = 0.300 {
         PRmap = { 1.420, 1.468, 1.516, 1.565, 1.613, 1.661, 1.709, 1.757, 1.805, 1.854, 1.902, 1.950 }
